about


I am a Senior Biostatistician at
Memorial Sloan
Kettering Cancer Center in New York City. I am also a DrPH candidate
in Biostatistics
at
Columbia University. My research interests include adaptive methods
in clinical trials, precision medicine, predictive modeling, and
prostate cancer screening methods. In my time away from work and school,
I enjoy baking, going to the beach, running, and programing in R.
